<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Introduction to HTML</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      margin: 2rem;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      color: #333;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #1a73e8;
    }
    a {
      color: #1a73e8;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>What is HTML?</h1>
  <p>HTML stands for <strong>HyperText Markup Language</strong>. It's the standard language used to create webpages.</p>

  <h2>Basic HTML Tags</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>&lt;h1&gt; to &lt;h6&gt;</code> – Headings</li>
    <li><code>&lt;p&gt;</code> – Paragraph</li>
    <li><code>&lt;a&gt;</code> – Link</li>
    <li><code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> – List</li>
    <li><code>&lt;img&gt;</code> – Image</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Each tag tells the browser how to display content.</p>

  <p><a href="css.html">Go to CSS Page →</a></p>
</body>
</html>

